I've heard that the state income tax exemption is meant to encourage businesses to stay in the state, but it seems like it's more of a handout to big corporations than anything else. And don't even get me started on the waste and inefficiency in government spending. I've seen firsthand how government contracts can be riddled with waste and abuse, and how politicians use them to reward their friends and allies. It's frustrating to see so much money being wasted when there are so many important needs that aren't being met.
